nodes.title: Infodump
widgets_values:
# What's this?
This is a tiled Image-To-Video upscaler, just like Ultimate SD Upscaler (USDU), except using high resolution start image which drives the video to higher quality while retaining the original details.

## Why not just using USDU?
When you want to increase more details, you need to increase denoise, but in turn, the video's original details will lost. That is why we should utilize I2V model, using high resolution start image to guide the models to retain the details **even with high denoise** that might have lost with typical T2V upscale model.

## The catch?
This upscaler works well, assuming you have the initial high resolution image. Also, context windows (for long videos) will not work for this unfortunately, but you could try USDU with T2V model (with lower denoise).

nodes.title: Infodump
widgets_values:
# How to use this?

Download the models as listed in this configuration. Using GGUF or FP8 model also works and maybe faster for you. You can combine this with any compatible low noise Lightx2v lora, which gains more speed with only few steps.

---
## Settings:
- **CFG:** 1.0 (with lightx2v lora)
- **Shift:** 1
- **Sampler/Scheduler:** res_multistep/beta (more detailed)
- **Denoise value:** 0.5-0.3 (higher values bring out more details but potentially have some artifact)
- **Sharpen radius:** 1 (use 0 if too sharp)
- **Steps:** 3-5 (higher means more details, but also slower)
- **Scale factor:** 1.5-3 (more means longer obviously)
- **Tile:** 3x2 or 2x2 (depending on scale factor)
- **Padding:** 64px (can go higher if seams are noticeable)
---
## Pre-upscaler model:
- 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.pth (more detailed, slower processing)
- 4x_ClearReality (faster processing)
---
## Lightx2v LoRA:
- **2.1 lightx2v i2v 480p rank 256** (produce sharper video but sometimes blocky artifacts)
- **2.1 lightx2v t2v 0.15 quantile** (produce smoother image with some details)
- **2.1 lightx2v (t2v/i2v 480) rank 64** (lighter, easier to run, but lose a bit of quality)
